  You’re invited to join us on our INCAS “ Hamburg Weekend ” from 7th to 9th October . 
 
  Hamburg is the second biggest city Germany and is located the north of the country at the North Sea . The canals , rivers , and lakes and around Hamburg create unique environment . 
  The city stands out through its cultural and historical variety . Take the opportunity to visit one of the largest ports Europe , Hamburg -PRON- famous nightlife district Reeperbahn or the UNESCO World Heritage Site at the harbour , the Speicherstadt and the Kontorhausviertel . 
 
  On the first day , we take our privat double-decker bus to Hamburg . On arrival we check into the Meininger Hostel and move into our rooms . Afterwards we have two-hour guided city tour on the bus to experience Hamburg at one go . On the next day we take two hour boat trip during which we see the hidden sights and the most beautiful spots the inner city from the water . In the afternoon you have the possibility either to explore Hamburg on your own or to take part our optional program . 
  Before we return back to Aachen we have another guided city tour the ancient city of Lüneburg , which could be preserved from the damages during World sein II and is famous for its surrounding natural landscape , the ‘ Lüneburger Heide’ .

  Artworks , talks , discussions , rehearsals , and performances various constellations of documents and prospects offer multitude of encounters with the public for negotiating the way of the world from 1989 to today , and thinking beyond .

Opening FANTASIE With works by Henning Bohl , Nicola Brunnhuber , Stephan Dillemuth , Isabelle Fein , Jutta Koether , Chris Kraus , Frances Scholz , Anne Speier and Raphaela Vogel 

  The exhibition " Fantasie " belongs to three-part series which be continued 2017 . It pursues interest that already the starting point of considerations of two shows at hallen Kunst : On the one hand , the interest the moment of ambiguity and ambivalence contemporary art ( " On Radical Juxtaposition " , 2014 ) , on the other , the interest Kenneth Anger -PRON- notion of film and therefore of cultural and artistic production as magic ritual , which appears contrary to what today manifests itself as both deeply ambivalent and questionable art field permeated by economic and power interests ( " Magic Lantern Cycle " , 2015 ) . 

  While the first part of the series engages with the concept of imagination , the second turns to the notions of authentic - inauthentic and the third to gestures and expression . all three are grasped as interconnected aspects of thinking about artistic practice and are based on the attempt to find concepts for those moments that interest one works of art – i.e. , to positively designate aspects that are met with interest and response , and not only to use negation to formulate the fact that quite bit of contemporary art exhausts itself to high degree running through references , evoking critical impetus , vocabulary schooled discourse , or glossy superficiality . Surprisingly , this attempt has brought notions to the fore that are regarded as rather obsolete and reactionary ( imagination , authenticity , expression ) . Which is turn interesting , too , because it seems to reveal desire to utilize these concepts for contemporary art as well , since they can apparently name something that has to do with the surplus value and essence of art , meaning not just knowledge and experience , but the ability to generate intensities . The exhibition series therefore seeks to approach these notions with the awareness of how they are charged and how questionable they are , beyond clichéd understanding , order to find out how far and which direction they can take us . However , the situation has become more complicated recent years . Against the background of increasingly stronger criticism of emptied critical or politicized art practices , evoking these moments may not be generally suspected of contributing to hopelessly antiquated concept of art anymore ; but the wake of the critique of the " political as style " ( James Meyer ) , one must now be careful not to allow " new sensibility " , " intensity as style " , to creep , based on the reactivation of notion of the autonomy of art restricted to the formal . 

  Imagination is first of all the foundation of all cognition , for according to Aristoteles , the soul does not think without images . Although it is moment that constructs reality , there is difference between images of mathematical or philosophical deliberations , for example , that ultimately remain imaginary , and those of artistic production during which one -PRON- imagination transfers imaginary images to real images . Even if – or precisely because – this is basically true of all artistic practices , the interest guiding the exhibition goes beyond merely ascertaining this fact and aims at artistic works that quite explicitly address imagination as desire , as the driving force of artistic production , without seeking to control it ; works that do not shy away from the imagination on which they are based and thus integrate voids , incalculability , affects , and desire . Alongside such basic considerations , the focus is on art fueled by imagination that seeks what is possible as opposed to what exists . At issue is the development and invention of worlds , languages , and spheres that situate themselves next to or beyond reality ( toward fantasy and fiction ) . Appropriating the world by inventing the world . This immediately gives rise to the question of whether imagination is possibility to create alternativ to and descriptions of what exists , or whether it is to be regarded more as escapist withdrawal into privat universes and thus " worldless " , to use Hannah Arendt -PRON- words . And does such art immediately make itself vulnerable , because the accusation of Marxist art critique applies to it , namely , that revolving around sentiments , inwardness , affects , and one -PRON- own artist -PRON- position follows late-capitalist logics ? What would regressive concept of imagination be , and where does the border to progressive one lie ? If proximity to Harald Szeemann -PRON- individual mythologies arises here , then the constitutive ( and constructive ) function of imagination for the sphere of the political must be marked . The latter has been increasingly discussed recent years , most intensively the series " Phantasm and Politics " organized by Helmut Draxler and Christoph Gurk at HAU ( Hebbel ufern ) Berlin . Freud , and later Lacan , already stressed the constitutive role of the imaginary ( Lacan used the term phantasm ) , albeit for the human psyche and the resulting construction of reality ( or what are regearded as such ) . This aspect of constituting , which is characteristic of imagination , already makes it clear that the exhibition is not about ( and cannot be about ) establishing dubious opposition between imagination and concept , and thus contributing to naturalization , for the reason that thought and imagination always have the samen origin , since one cannot be had without the other . Hence , imagination as such is never essentialist , even if it is at times essentialized . Yet , like with the " fantasia " as form of musical composition , it is accompanied by associations of emotionality and expressivity , creating opening that leads away from the here and now . so if , according to Christina Braun , imaginary spaces are zones of inaccessibility and incalculability , and imagination is thus the retaining of spheres " that needn’t correspond with the world , that make no claim to reality , meaning that they do not lay claim to the possibility of becoming material or visible " , what does this tell us about art ?   Mastermind Ferdy Doernberg ( known as band member of AXEL RUDI PELL as well ) teamed up with André Hort ( bass ) , Mike Mandel ( guitars ) and Alex wenn ( drums ) , who are young and hungry musicians from the Hanover-area to bring fresh blood and enthusiasm into the band and most important to bring back more Metal into ROUGH SILK -PRON- sound again ! so with the anniversary the new album start new era for the band and you can .. t name it better then with the album title : A New Beginning ! 

  ROUGH SILK were founded 1989 and have released seven studio and one best of album far their history . During all these years the band has defined their very unique sound which is best described by the band name ROUGH SILK : " Rough " stands for the real heavy ( sometimes even Thrash- and Death- ) Metal influences and " Silk " for the unusual singer-songwriter elements and piano-parts , combining both to their very own brand of heavy but yet Melodic Metal .

  Gostaríamos de convidá-los para o nosso grupo de conversação em português ( e alemão ) , que se encontra toda terça-feira , partir 20h30 , no bar/restaurante " Lebenslust " , Erich-Kästner-Str . 14 ( esquina com Herzogstr . , perto estação de metrô U2 Hohenzollernplatz ) . Falamos português do Brasil , de Portugal e até de Angola , em todos os níveis , mas também há espaço para quem se interessa pelos países lusófonos e ( ainda ) não domina língua portuguesa , preferindo conversar em alemão , assim como para brasileiros , portugueses , angolanos etc. que queiram praticar o alemão . Somos pessoas bem diversas , do mundo inteiro e de todas as idades , e sempre se acha alguém para bater bom papo . Temos em comum o nosso interesse pela língua e cultura desses países , seja porque nascemos ou vivemos ali , viajamos ou queremos viajar para lá , ou simplesmente porque gostamos de falar e ouvir o idioma português , assim como adoramos escutar música brasileira e portuguesa ...

  CHB presented its Conduction series 2016 . ﻿A part of the program , CHB presents the next concert event on 12 October , which reflects on Béla Bartók´s work . The evening concert is separated again into two different parts : it kicks off with the classical section with original compositions interpreted by the Classicus Quartet , followed by improvisational contemporary concert of the CHB Orchestra which this time be led by Samu Gryllus . The evening commemorates for the 135th anniversary of Béla Bartók -PRON- birthdate . 

  Classicus Quartet ( József Rácz and Réka Baksai on violins , Péter Tornyai on viola and Tamás Zétényi playing cello ) is string quartet dedicated to the string quartet repertoire from Bartók . The quartet -PRON- recent performances include the premier of László Dobszay -PRON- string quartet , concert at the Bartók Festival Ankara , concert at the Esterházy Palace Fertőd , appearances at CEU , and many more .

  The CHB -PRON- resident orchestra , formed 2016 , has already met twice huge success with the conduction of Jean-Paul Bourelly and Renée Baker . This time , on 12 October the orchestra is going to reflect to the infamous music of Bartók , while Samu Gryllus conducts them with the alloy of Soundpainting .

  Conduction ( full name : conducted improvisation ) developed by Lawrence D. „ Butch “ Morris ( 1947 - 2013 ) , American cornetist , jazz musician , composer and conductor . Conduction is type of free improvisation where the conductor directs improvising ensemble with series of hand and baton gestures . 
  Soundpainting is similar „ sign language ” for musicians through which the condutor connects the musicians’ improvisational melodies with the aim of creating one joint composition . Soundpainting developed by Walter Thompson 1974 , New York . It keeps the improvisational music strictly structured with the help of hundreds of hand and baton gestures . One of the most important contemporary , Hungarian representative of the Soundpainting method is Samu Gryllus , who is going to conduct the ensemble this evening with mixture Conduction and Soundpainting sings , taking unique middle course between the two rival methods .
